tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review: Hi, would like to post my experience with Dr Vishnu at Ethos Dental clinic, Narsingi. I had a bad tooth ache, so I went here. Dr told it was because of the wisdom tooth, and had formed some infection around. He took a pen and paper to explain the issue in detail, suggedted me to get the tooth removed., gave me ample time to decide if I want to go ahead, explained the cost and other details and gave next day's appointment to do the procedure. I decided to go ahead with the procedure, and went next day on time. He started the procedure on time. He reassured am ready for it, had patiently done the process, let me take my time to go through the pain, did not hurry me at all, which was the best part. He very confidently closed the procedure within the said time, and post procedure explained my next steps to do, precautions to take, and was constantly in touch through what's app, answering all my questions. He gave a follow up appointment post a week, ensured I did absolutely ok. What more could one ask for ? For any dental issues, feel free to go to Ethos clinic to meet Dr Vishnu. He is great at his work and helps us handle pain with comfort. Thank you very much Dr.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
context: Orthognathic Surgery,Dental Braces Fixing,Surgical Tooth Extraction,
review:
My family consulted me about Dr. Vishnu and asked me to visit him.

I was in the final phase of braces removal and was earlier showing to clove, Manikonda, that is when before removing my braces, they asked to have tooth extraction and implantation which was costing me bomb there. I am not saying doctors were bad there, it was just that it was really busy in clove.

Then I consulted him and he said he can do the same at reasonable price and did it neatly. Also I got my braces removed finally today and retainers have been put.

Best thing is, I did not had to wait for hours to get it done..

I would highly recommend to come and visit this doctor if there is any dental issue.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Wait time,
review: This visit was for my wife. She was having pain and bleeding in her gums for a week. Doctor her examined her gums and then suggested for x-ray. X-ray was available in clinic. So it was quick. He then told that there is no problem in teeth or gum. There is nothing to worry about. Then he did tooth scaling. It was really painful. Doctor explained that he went a bit deep in gums for cleaning that's why it was painful. He recommended an antibiotic and a gel to apply on gums. He asked us to visit after 1 week for rechecking. My wife was getting relief after 3-4 days. After 1 week, she was fine. We went to doctor after 1 week. He examined again and said it's all okay.
